# HarmonyOS App Initialization Flow

## When To Use

Apply this flow when the task is explicitly about creating, initializing, scaffolding, cloning, or first-time wiring a new top-level `app-*` HarmonyOS application in this workspace.

Examples:

- create a new `app-*` application
- initialize a reminder app / dashboard app / business app
- scaffold a new child app and make it appear in `app-center`
- clone an existing app as the starting point for a new app

Do not use this flow for routine edits inside an already-established app unless the task also changes workspace-level app registration.

## Naming And Placement

- New apps must use the `app-` prefix.
- New apps must live directly under repository root as `app-*/`.
- Do not create HarmonyOS build files at repository root.

## Required App Skeleton

Every initialized app must include at least:

- `AppScope/`
- `entry/`
- `build-profile.json5`
- `oh-package.json5`
- `hvigorfile.ts`
- `app.json`
- `dev-build.sh`
- `dev-start.sh`
- `dev-stop.sh`
- `run-start.sh`
- `dev-build.bat`
- `dev-start.bat`
- `dev-stop.bat`
- `run-start.bat`
- `scripts/common.sh`
- `scripts/common.bat`

## Preferred Initialization Method

- Prefer cloning the closest existing `app-*` scaffold instead of generating files from scratch.
- After cloning, immediately rewrite app identity:
  - directory name
  - `app.json`
  - `AppScope/app.json5`
  - resource strings
  - bundle name
  - labels and app-specific text
- Remove copied transient artifacts from the new app before verification:
  - `.deveco-sdk-shim/`
  - `.hvigor/`
  - `build/`
  - `entry/build/`

## Workspace Registration

When a new app is initialized:

- add it to `app-center/app.json`:
  - `dependsOn`
  - `launchTargets`
- add a visible management card entry in `app-center/entry/src/main/ets/pages/Index.ets`
- keep the default workspace model:
  - `app-center` remains the desktop-visible main entry
  - new child apps are hidden from desktop by default unless the task explicitly says otherwise
- update sibling app `dependsOn` only when the workspace convention expects the new app to be part of the shared base set

## App-Level Requirement Capture

- Create `REQ.md` inside the new `app-*` directory when the task is initializing a new business app or new product requirement.
- `REQ.md` should capture:
  - app positioning
  - core goals
  - target users
  - MVP scope
  - workspace integration expectations

## Verification Minimum

Initialization is not complete until these checks are attempted:

- build the new app:
  - Unix: `cd <new-app> && ./dev-build.sh`
  - Windows: `cd <new-app> && dev-build.bat`
- build the center:
  - Unix: `cd app-center && ./dev-build.sh`
  - Windows: `cd app-center && dev-build.bat`
- if simulator/device is available, start the center:
  - Unix: `cd app-center && ./dev-start.sh`
  - Windows: `cd app-center && dev-start.bat`
- confirm the new app can at least be installed and managed through `app-center`

If simulator or device verification is blocked, state that explicitly.

## Documentation Sync

When a new `app-*` is initialized, update the early-load docs:

- `CLAUDE.md`
- `CODEX.md`
- `AGENTS.md` if startup guidance or app inventory changed
- the relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files when app inventory or initialization workflow changed
